# Raw feature collections — committing these would add a non-trivial amount
# of git history per fetch. For CO, the CPW FeatureServer layer 6 (Big Game
# GMUs, ~186 polygons) is on the order of 5-10MB per fetch. Future CWD-zone
# and restricted-area layers (S05.3 / S05.4) may scale higher. Uniform
# discipline with MT (where MT FWP feature payloads exceed 180MB/run across
# layers #3, #10, #11) keeps the policy decision simple — the gitignore
# rule is identical to MT's per the ArcGIS Fidelity SHOULD-FIX.
#
# Metadata files (~7KB each) ARE committed for drift detection on field
# names, OID columns, and spatialReference. Manifests (~5KB each) ARE
# committed for per-fetch checksum / cross-operator drift detection (see
# the S02.7 manifest schema in docs/runbooks/E02-geometry-verification.md).
# No glob rule is needed to permit them — this comment anchors the policy.
*-features-*.geojson

# Atomic-write tmp files orphaned by interrupted writes (rare).
*.tmp

# Raw PDF source documents — committing these would add ~MB per fetch to git
# (the 2026 CPW Big Game brochure alone is ~96.7MB / 84 pages). Per S06.1
# (mirrors S03.1), PDFs stay local-only, paired with a committed per-fetch
# *-pdf-manifest.json carrying SHA-256, page count, and source provenance.
*.pdf

# Drift-detection marker files written when SHA-256 of a re-fetch differs from
# the committed manifest. The operator deletes the marker after acknowledging
# the drift; until then, downstream extraction stories (S06.3 / S06.4 / S06.5)
# refuse to proceed. Markers are runtime state, not committed artifacts.
*-pending-reextraction.flag

# Per-PDF manifests (S06.1) — *-pdf-manifest.json (~1KB each) ARE committed for
# cross-operator drift detection. No glob rule is needed since manifests don't
# match *.pdf — this comment anchors the policy.
